.TH "xemaclite_aligned_read" 9 "xemaclite_aligned_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xemaclite_aligned_read \- Read from 32-bit aligned to 16-bit aligned buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xemaclite_aligned_read
.BI "(u32 *src_ptr "  ","
.BI "u8 *dest_ptr "  ","
.BI "unsigned length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src_ptr" 12
Pointer to the 32-bit aligned source address
.IP "dest_ptr" 12
Pointer to the 16-bit aligned destination address
.IP "length" 12
Number bytes to read from source to destination
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function reads data from a 32-bit aligned address in the EmacLite device
to a 16-bit aligned buffer.
